CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 11, 1969, pg. 16 reads:"Distinguished Four - The photographer was right on hand to get this picture of four very important sorors during the AKA Ball at the William Penn Hotel. They are from left: Janet Thompson, basileus; Altha Brown of Wilberforce, Ohio; Laura Cooper, basileus-elect, and Emilene Hayes, chairman of the social committee which was in charge of the ball."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of four Alpha Kappa Alpha members, from left: Janet Thompson, Altha Brown, Laura Cooper, and Emilene Hayes, posed in William Penn Hotel during holiday formal
